Hydroxyproline is specifically formed through the hydroxylation of proline during collagen synthesis, requiring vitamin C as a cofactor. While proline is part of the collagen backbone, hydroxyproline becomes an integral component that stabilizes the triple helical structure of collagen. Its concentration directly reflects collagen content since it is uniquely derived from proline in the collagen-specific synthetic pathway.

